#30178
Thorn-Black Hedgerow~
Somewhere beyond sight, a funeral bell answers itself in staggered peals, as if two towers now stand where one once was. Briars trained like vineyard rows have gone feral here; they knot around old fencing in cathedral arches and hook at your clothes as you pass. Across Thorn-Black Hedgerow, lengths of black ribbon are nailed to posts at shoulder height, snapping in the wind like a line of muttered refusals.~
